<br>
Of anything else, the closest to a viable/popular alternative is 46 BS, 39 weapon, then you can raise parry to somewhere around 30 with the extra points. Now this keeps your songs in tact, raises your defense alot, but at a signifigant dent to your dammage output. Also parry is halved against dual wield/LW, and not effective in large melees. Basically, 1 on 1 this is a good spec path, but in actual practice is not near as good.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=durgrim>Durgrim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/13/02 1:24:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=356.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Thanks!</span><hr size=1> Looks like I'll stay the course for the time being and use 46/47/leftover.<br>
